   <concept id="FAR_19_1406" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">19.1406</ph> 
         Sole source awards.
      </title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d1245e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1279e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
						             A contracting officer shall consider a contract award to a SDVOSB concern on a sole source basis (see <xref href="6.302-5.dita#FAR_6_302_5"
                        base="i1119624"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">6.302-5</xref>(b)(6)), before considering small business set-asides (see <xref href="19.203.dita#FAR_19_203"
                        base="i1101696"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.203</xref> and subpart <xref href="Subpart_19.5.dita#FAR_Subpart_19_5"
                        base="i1100723"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.5</xref>) provided none of the exclusions of <xref href="19.1404.dita#FAR_19_1404"
                        base="i1099419"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.1404</xref> apply and—</p>
               <ol id="d1245e35" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1279e28">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
								                 The contracting officer does not have a reasonable expectation that offers would be received from two or more service-disabled veteran-owned small business concerns;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1279e33">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
								                 The anticipated award price of the contract, including options, will not exceed-</p>
                     <ol id="d1245e54" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d1279e39">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              <ph rev="FAC 2025-06 October 1, 2025" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2024-001?>$8.5 million<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 19.1406 by—   a. Removing from paragraph (a)(2)(i) “$7 million” and adding “$8.5 million” in its place; and?></ph> for a requirement within the NAICS codes for manufacturing; or</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d1279e44">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              <ph rev="FAC 2025-06 October 1, 2025" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2024-001?>$5 million<?FM MARKER [Why] b. Removing from paragraph (a)(2)(ii) “$4 million” and adding “$5 million” in its place.?></ph> for a requirement within any other NAICS code;</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1279e49">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
								                 The requirement is not currently being performed by an 8(a) participant under the provisions of <xref href="Subpart_19.8.dita#FAR_Subpart_19_8"
                              base="i1099848"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  19.8</xref> or has been accepted as a requirement by SBA under <xref href="Subpart_19.8.dita#FAR_Subpart_19_8"
                              base="i1099848"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  19.8</xref>;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1279e60">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        
								                 The service-disabled veteran-owned small business concern has been determined to be a responsible contractor with respect to performance; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1279e65">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph>
                        
								                 Award can be made at a fair and reasonable price.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1282e73">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> Effective January 1, 2024, a contracting officer shall only award a sole-source contract to a concern that— </p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1282e82">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        Is designated in SAM as an SDVOSB concern certified by SBA; or
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1282e88">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        Has represented that it is an SDVOSB concern in SAM and submitted an application for certification to SBA on or before December 31, 2023. Pending applications for certification are in the SBA Veteran Small Business Certification Program database at <xref href="https://veterans.certify.sba.gov"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">https://veterans.certify.sba.gov</xref>.
                     </p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1279e70">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph> The SBA has the right to appeal the contracting officer’s decision not to make an SDVOSB sole-source award. </p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
